iantes Tecos|UAG]]\n| managerclubs5 = [[Club Atlas|Atlas]]\n| managerclubs6 = [[Quer\u00e9taro F.C.|Quer\u00e9taro]]\n| managerclubs7 = [[Santos Laguna]]\n| managerclubs8 = [[Tigres de la UANL|UANL]]\n| managerclubs9 = [[Puebla F.C.|Puebla]]\n| managerclubs10 = [[Atlante F.C.|Atlante]]\n| managerclubs11 = [[Club Tijuana|Tijuana]]\n| managerclubs12 = [[Club Universidad de Guadalajara|UdeG]]\n| managerclubs13 = [[Tampico Madero]]\n| pcupdate = \n| ntupdate = \n| medaltemplates       = \n{{MedalCountry | {{flagu|Mexico}} }}\n{{medalRU|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica]]|[[1993 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1993]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Daniel Guzm\u00e1n Casta\u00f1eda''' (born December 31, 1965 in [[Guadalajara, Jalisco|Guadalajara]]) is a retired [[Mexican people|Mexican]] professional [[Association football|football]] player. Nicknamed \"[[Dennis the Menace (U.S. comics)|El Travieso]],\" he played for 15 years for various clubs in Mexico. His son [[Daniel Guzm\u00e1n Jr.]] is also a football player.\n\n==Honours==\n===Player===\n;UdeG\n*[[Copa MX|Copa M\u00e9xico]]: [[1990\u201391 Copa M\u00e9xico|1990\u201391]]\n\n;Atlante\n*[[Liga MX|Mexican Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]: [[1992\u201393 Mexican Primera Divisi\u00f3n season|1992\u201393]]\n\n===Manager===\n;Santos Laguna\n*[[Liga MX|Mexican Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]: [[Primera Divisi\u00f3n de M\u00e9xico Clausura 2008|Clausura 2008]]\n\n;UANL\n*[[North American SuperLiga]]: [[2009 North American SuperLiga|2009]]\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFT player|14504}}\n* {{Webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090221230546/http://web.mlsnet.com/history/register.jsp?content=players_g |title=MLS All-Time Player Register }}\n\n{{Mexico Squad 1993 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Daniel Guzm\u00e1n managerial positions\n|list1=\n{{Club Deportivo Guadalajara managers}}\n{{Atlas F.C. managers}}\n{{Santos Laguna managers}}\n{{Tigres UANL managers}}\n{{Club Tijuana managers}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Guzman, Daniel}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living peo