upeita-lautakunnan.html\n|title= Enimm\u00e4kseen upeita lautakunnan kokouskuulumisia 21.8.2008\n|accessdate= 2008-08-21\n|last= Haltia-Holmberg\n|first= Mirva\n|date= 2008-08-21\n|work= Haltian vaaliy\u00f6\n|language= Finnish\n|ref=Haltia-Holmberg 2008-08-21}}\n* {{cite web\n|url=http://haltia.blogspot.com/2008/09/ykknen-riesasta-ongelmanratkaisijaksi.html\n|title=Ykk\u00f6nen, riesasta ongelmanratkaisijaksi\n|accessdate= 2008-09-25\n|last= Haltia-Holmberg\n|first= Mirva\n|date= 2008-09-15\n|work= Haltian vaaliy\u00f6\n|language= Finnish\n|ref=Haltia-Holmberg 2008-09-15}}\n* {{cite web\n|url=http://haltia.blogspot.com/2008/12/kokouskuulumiset-joukkoliikennelautakun.html\n|title=Kokouskuulumiset: joukkoliikennelautakunta 11.12.2208\n|accessdate=14 December 2008\n|last= Haltia-Holmberg\n|first= Mirva\n|date=11 December 2008\n|work= Haltian vaaliy\u00f6\n|language= Finnish\n|ref=Haltia-Holmberg 2008-12-11}}\n* {{cite web\n|url=http://haltia.blogspot.com/2009/04/hkln-johtokunnan-kokouskuulumiset.html\n|title=HKL:n johtokunnan kokouskuulumiset 30.4.2009\n|accessdate=2009-05-04\n|last= Haltia-Holmberg\n|first= Mirva\n|date=2009-04-30\n|work= Haltian kiskoty\u00f6\n|language= Finnish\n|ref=Haltia-Holmberg 2009-04-30}}\n* {{cite web\n|url= http://www.hel.fi/static/public/hela/Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta/Suomi/Esitys/2007/Ksv_2007-06-07_Kslk_20_El/071550252/Jatkasaaren_joukkoliikenteen_jarjestaminen.html\n|title= J\u00e4tk\u00e4saaren joukkoliikenteen j\u00e4rjest\u00e4minen\n|accessdate= 2008-08-20\n|publisher= Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta\n|date= 2007-06-08\n|language= Finnish\n|ref= Kslk 2007-1011\n|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070905051054/http://www.hel.fi/static/public/hela/Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta/Suomi/Esitys/2007/Ksv_2007-06-07_Kslk_20_El/071550252/Jatkasaaren_joukkoliikenteen_jarjestaminen.html\n|archive-date= 2007-09-05\n|url-status= dead\n}}\n* {{cite web\n|url=http://www.hel.fi/static/public/hela/Joukkoliikennelautakunta/Suomi/Esitys/2008/HKL_2008-12-11_Jlk_30_El/79DDF823-50AB-41B7-ABC3-24881954F83F/30suy2Liite1Uudet_linjastokuvat.pdf\n|title= J\u00e4tk\u00e4saaren joukkoliikenne 2015/2025\n|accessdate= 14 December 2008\n|publisher= Joukkoliikennelautakunta\n|date= 11 December 2008\n|language= Finnish\n|format=[[PDF]]\n|ref=JLK 2008-12-11}}\n* {{cite web\n |url         = http://www.vantaansanomat.fi/Uutiset/Arkisto/2009/02/20/Helsingin-liitosalue-saattaa-jaada-kokonaan-ilman-metroa\n |title       = Helsingin liitosalue saattaa j\u00e4\u00e4d\u00e4 kokonaan ilman metroa\n |accessdate  = 2009-02-26\n |last        = Karjalainen\n |first       = Marketta\n |date        = 2009-02-20\n |work        = Vantaan Sanomat\n |language    = Finnish\n |ref         = Karjalainen 2009-02-20\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20110720194510/http://www.vantaansanomat.fi/Uutiset/Arkisto/2009/02/20/Helsingin-liitosalue-saattaa-jaada-kokonaan-ilman-metroa\n |archivedate = 2011-07-20\n}}\n* {{cite web\n|url=http://www.hel2.fi/ksv/julkaisut/julk_2008-10.pdf\n|format=PDF\n|title=Laajasalon raidevaihtoehtojen j\u00e4rjestelm\u00e4tarkastelu 2008\n|accessdate=2008-10-04\n|publisher=Helsingin kaupunkisuunnitteluvirasto\n|date= 2008-10-02\n|language= Finnish\n|ref=KSVLaajasalo}}\n* {{cite web\n|url= http://www.hel.fi/static/public/hela/Joukkoliikennelautakunta/Suomi/Esitys/2008/HKL_2008-08-21_Jlk_19_El/AF950094-7BCF-43AC-8E43-835E7497204F/LAUSUNTO_VALTUUSTOALOITTEESTA_(WALLDEN-PAULIG)_KOS.html\n|title= Lausunto valtuustoaloitteesta (Wallden-Paulig) koskien etel\u00e4isen Helsingin joukkoliikenneyhteyden palauttamista\n|accessdate= 2008-08-18\n|publisher= Joukkoliikennelautakunta\n|date= 2008-08-08\n|language= Finnish\n|ref=notemisc20}}\n* {{cite web\n |url        = http://www.epaper.fi/reader/?issue=5828;eb73b7942ee89488b3684b9d5bd9a136\n |title      = Joukkoliikennekadun tilalle tarjotaan kampusratikkaa\n |last       = Marttinen\n |first      = Vesa\n |accessdate = 2009-03-08\n |publisher  = Helsingin Uutiset\n |date       = 2009-03-07\n |page       = 4\n |language   = Finnish\n |ref        = helsingin_uutiset\n}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n* {{cite web\n |url         = http://yle.fi/alueet/helsinki/uusimaa/2009/06/pikaraitiotieta_kaavaillaan_porvooseen_asti_824513.html\n |title       = Pikaraitiotiet\u00e4 kaavaillaan Porvooseen asti\n |accessdate  = 2009-07-02\n |date        = 2009-06-25\n |publisher   = [[YLE]]\n |language    = Finnish\n |ref         = YLE 2009-06-25\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20100818192905/http://yle.fi/alueet/helsinki/uusimaa/2009/06/pikaraitiotieta_kaavaillaan_porvooseen_asti_824513.html\n |archivedate = 2010-08-18\n}}\n* {{cite web\n |url         = http://www.hel.fi/wps/wcm/connect/63d70f804a173602b61afe3d8d1d4668/JOUKKOLIIKENNELAUTAKUNTA+17.6.2008.doc?MOD=AJPERES\n |title       = P\u00e4\u00e4t\u00f6stiedote\n |accessdate  = 2008-06-30\n |date        = 2008-06-17\n |format      = [[Microsoft Word|DOC]]\n |publisher   = Joukkoliikennelautakunta\n |language    = Finnish\n |ref         = notemisc10\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20110611100553/http://www.hel.fi/wps/wcm/connect/63d70f804a173602b61afe3d8d1d4668/JOUKKOLIIKENNELAUTAKUNTA+17.6.2008.doc?MOD=AJPERES\n |archivedate = 2011-06-11\n}}\n* {{cite web\n|url=http://www.hel.fi/static/public/hela/Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta/Suomi/Pikayhteenveto/2009/Ksv_2009-04-02_Kslk_11_Pi_I/688FB119-E61E-409B-A984-E4A914B7B60F/11-02042009.html?CACHEPARAM=Ksv%202009-04-02%20Kslk%2011%20Pi%20I?\n|title=P\u00e4\u00e4t\u00f6stiedote 2.4.2009\n|accessdate=2009-04-03\n|publisher= Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta\n|date=2009-04-02\n|language= Finnish\n|ref=KSLK 2009-04-02}}\n* {{cite web\n |url         = http://www.hel2.fi/paatoksenteko/kvsto-tiedote/index.html\n |title       = P\u00e4\u00e4t\u00f6stiedote nr 20\n |accessdate  = 13 November 2008\n |date        = 12 November 2008\n |publisher   = Helsingin kaupunginvaltuusto\n |language    = Finnish\n |ref         = KV 2008-11-12\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20090520092549/http://www.hel2.fi/paatoksenteko/kvsto-tiedote/index.html\n |archivedate = 20 May 2009\n}}\n* {{cite web\n|url= http://www.hel2.fi/ksv/hela/Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta/Esityslistat/053460225.htm#P4168_260134\n|title= Raide-Jokerin alustava yleissuunnitelma, suunnittelun ja mitoituksen l\u00e4ht\u00f6kohdat\n|accessdate= 2008-07-16\n|publisher= Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta\n|date= 2005-12-15\n|language= Finnish\n|ref= notemisc15\n|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070702165949/http://www.hel2.fi/ksv/hela/Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta/Esityslistat/053460225.htm#P4168_260134\n|archive-date= 2007-07-02\n|url-status= dead\n}}\n* {{cite web\n|url= http://www.hel2.fi/ksv/hela/Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta/Esityslistat/liitteet/061310695.pdf\n|title= RATIKKA 2015 \u2013 vaihtoehdot\n|accessdate= 2008-06-24\n|format= PDF\n|publisher= Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta\n|language= Finnish\n|ref= notemisc13\n|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20090318013247/http://www.hel2.fi/ksv/hela/Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta/Esityslistat/liitteet/061310695.pdf\n|archive-date= 2009-03-18\n|url-status= dead\n}}\n* {{cite web\n|url=http://lotta.yle.fi/rsweb2.nsf/sivut/uutisaihe?opendocument&pageid=Content075003A6872\n|title=Valtuutetut pen\u00e4\u00e4v\u00e4t ysilinjalle muutoksia\n|accessdate=2008-10-10\n|date=2008-10-10\n|format= \n|work=Ylen aikaisen uutiset\n|publisher=[[YLE]]\n|language= Finnish\n|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081012114131/http://lotta.yle.fi/rsweb2.nsf/sivut/uutisaihe?opendocument&pageid=Content075003A6872\n|archivedate=2008-10-12\n|ref=ylen_aikainen}}\n* {{cite web\n |url         = http://raidejokeri.info/Raportti/Raide-Jokeri_raportti.pdf\n |title       = Raide-Jokeri Alustava yleissuunnitelma 2009\n |accessdate  = 2010-11-06\n |date        = May 2009\n |format      = PDF\n |publisher   = [[Helsinki|The City of Helsinki]], [[Espoo|The City of Espoo]], [[Helsinki Metropolitan Area Council]], Ministry of Transport and Communications\n |language    = Finnish\n |ref         = raidejokeri_info_report\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20110721231830/http://raidejokeri.info/Raportti/Raide-Jokeri_raportti.pdf\n |archivedate = 2011-07-21\n}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|Trams in Helsinki}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.hel.fi/hki/HKL/en/Etusivu|Helsinki City Transport official website}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130729073424/http://www.hsl.fi/FI/aikataulutjareitit/Documents/ratikka_13.8.2012.pdf Tram line route map] (Official map {{As of|2012|8|13|alt=as of 2012}})\n* [http://www.hsl.fi/FI/aikataulutjareitit/Documents/HSL_ratikka+pysakit_13.8.2012.pdf Tram line route map with stops]{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} (Official map {{As of|2012|8|13|alt=as of 2012}})\n* [http://www.raidejokeri.info/ Raide-Jokeri] (Official website)\n\n[[Category:Transport in Helsinki]]\n[[Category:Tram transport in Finland]]\n[[Category:Proposed railway lines in Finland]]\n", "text_old": "[[Image:Helsinki tram map planned 2010-2025.png|thumb|Decided and proposed expansions to the Helsinki tram network. Existing tracks in dark green and grey.]]\nThe city of Helsinki has plans for a radical expansion of the tram network within the 2021\u20132035 time horizon, as laid out in the Helsinki City Plan, approved by the City Council in October 2016.<ref>http://www.yleiskaava.fi/en/city-plan/</ref> Below is a list of confirmed and proposed future expansions of the network. The largest confirmed projects are the {{convert|25|km|mi|adj=on}} trunk line 550 (\"Jokeri\") and the {{convert|10|km|mi|adj=on}} connection to the island of Laajasalo, which will include the longest bridge in Finland. Together, these two will effectively double the track length of the network.\n\n=={{anchor|reorganization}}Reorganisation of the tram lines==\n\nThe board of [[Helsingin seudun liikenne|HSL]] approved a plan for the reorganisation of the tram lines on 10 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hsl.fi/linjastosuunnitelmat/raitioliikenteen-linjastosuunnitelma|title=Raitioliikenteen linjastosuunnitelma|publisher=HSL|accessdate=2015-05-06}}</ref> The plan is meant to respond to the changing transportation needs as the new districts of the city in former brownfield sites (J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari, Hernesaari, Kalasatama, Keski-Pasila, Kruunuvuorenranta) are built. The reorganisation is to be carried out in stages in 2016\u20132024. The concept of the plan is to make the most of the existing track network and to assume only minimal construction of new track. According to the plan, the 2/3 and 7A/7B loops will be changed to linear routes and a new, short, peak-time line number 5 from Katajanokka ferry terminal to the Central Railway Station will serve ferry passengers. J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari will be served by lines 7, 8 and 9, and line 6 will be routed to the new district of Hernesaari. The tramway to the new district of Kruunuvuorenranta over a new, kilometre-long bridge was left to be planned separately, as the design of that line is dependent on a number of other decisions, including whether to close down the Hanasaari coal-fired power plant. The ten lines in 2024 according to the plan are as follows<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hsl.fi/sites/default/files/uploads/linjasto_2024.pdf|title=Raitioliikenteen linjastosuunnitelma, kokonaiskartta, tilanne 2024|publisher=HSL|accessdate=2015-05-06}}</ref> (see reference for a map):\n\n#[[Eira]] \u2013 [[K\u00e4pyl\u00e4]]\n#[[Olympia Terminal]] \u2013 [[L\u00e4nsi-Pasila]]\n#[[Olympia Terminal]] \u2013 [[Meilahti]]\n#[[Katajanokka]] \u2013 [[Munkkiniemi]]\n#[[Katajanokka Ferry Terminal]] \u2013 [[Helsinki Central Station|Central Railway Station]]\n# (6T: [[West Harbour, Helsinki|West Ferry Terminal]]) - [[Hietalahti, Helsinki|Hietalahti]] \u2013 [[Arabianranta|Arabia]]\n#[[West Harbour, Helsinki|West Ferry Terminal]] \u2013 [[L\u00e4nsi-Pasila]]\n#[[J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari]] \u2013 [[Arabianranta|Arabia]]\n#[[J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari]] \u2013 [[Pasila]]\n#[[Kirurgi Hospital|Kirurgi]] \u2013 [[Pikku Huopalahti]]\n\n==Improvements to the connectivity and capacity of the network==\n\nA number of short segments of new track in areas already covered by the network are being planned in order to improve the connectivity and capacity of the network.\n\n===Topeliuksenkatu===\n\nThe planned tracks would run along Topeliuksenkatu from Runeberginkatu to Mannerheimintie, in parallel to the tramway on Mannerheimintie. This would provide additional capacity and a faster route in the direction of Mannerheimintie. The Topeliuksenkatu tramway is widely considered to be a requirement for further extensions of lines 4 and 10, which include the Munkkivuori extension. This tramway was one of the proposals in a 2006 study named \"{{lang|fr|Ratikka 2015}}\" (\"Tram 2015\").\n<ref name=\"misc12\" /><ref name=\"FTS45\">[[#noteFTS45|Finnish Tramway Society]]</ref><ref name=\"misc13\">[[#notemisc13|Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta]]</ref>\n\n===Fredrikinkatu===\n\nIn Kamppi the tracks on the north and south ends of Fredrikinkatu are separated by a {{convert|530|m|mile|sigfig=1|adj=on}} gap.  New tracks are planned along Fredrikinkatu between the junctions at Bulevardi (south end) and Malminrinne/Urho Kekkosen katu (north end) to connect this gap and provide a parallel north-south connection to the congested main tramway along Mannerheimintie.\n\n==Extensions to new areas==\n\nThe opening of the [[Vuosaari Harbour]] in 2008 freed up harbour areas in J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari and Kalasatama near the city centre, as well as the oil terminal in Kruunuvuorenranta on the Laajasalo island, for development. A large rail yard in Pasila, which was used for handling freight rail traffic to J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari and Kalasatama, was also freed up. Helsinki is developing all four areas as new mixed-use urban districts, and in each case, the city decided to base the public transport in these areas on extensions to the tram network. (Pasila has a railway station that is served by all of the commuter trains, and Kalasatama has a metro station.)\n\n===J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari and Hernesaari===\n\nThe building of tramways in J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari has proceeded along with the construction of the buildings of the new district. The use of bi-directional trams was considered for the tramway extensions,<ref name=\"misc18\">[[#notemisc18|Antero Alku]]</ref> but in the end, HKL decided to build the tracks with conventional return loops and to dismantle temporary loops as necessary.\n\nAs of December 2017, only the final phase of the J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari tramways remains to be built, connecting the new ferry terminal in the southwestern corner of the island to the current return loop at Saukonpaasi (currently the terminus for lines 8 and 9). The completion of this stretch has been projected for 2025. In the previous phases, tracks were extended from Ruoholahti to Saukonpaasi (opened 1 January 2012), from Kamppi to the old ferry terminal (opened 13 August 2012), from the old to the new ferry terminal (opened February 2017) <ref>https://www.hel.fi/uutiset/fi/helsinki/lansisatama-uusi-terminaali</ref> and from J\u00e4tk\u00e4saarenlaituri along V\u00e4limerenkatu street to the return loop at Saukonpaasi (opened August 2017).\n\nVarious versions of the lines and routes to J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari have been proposed since the beginning of the planning.<ref name=\"misc12\">[[#notemisc12|Helsingin kaupungin liikennelaitos]]</ref><ref name=\"misc11\">[[#notemisc11|Helsingin kaupungin liikennelaitos]]</ref><ref name=\"JLK 2008-12-11\" /><ref name=\"Kslk 2007-1011\">[[#Kslk 2007-1011|Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta]]</ref><ref name=\"Haltia-Holmberg 2008-08-21\">[[#Haltia-Holmberg 2008-08-21|Mirva Haltia-Holmberg]]</ref> As of December 2017, lines 7, 8 and 9 are routed on J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari according to the plan approved in 2015 (see [[#reorganisation|Reorganisation]]). Line 6 awaits the completion of new tracks to Hernesaari. By 2025, line 6 will be rerouted from its current termini at Hietalahti and the J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari ferry terminal to Hernesaari via Eiranranta.<ref name=\"JLK 2008-12-11\">[[#JLK 2008-12-11|Joukkoliikennelautakunta]]</ref><ref name=\"Haltia-Holmberg 2008-12-11\">[[#Haltia-Holmberg 2008-12-11|Mirva Haltia-Holmberg]]</ref> The stretch to Eiranranta is projected to be completed in 2018 and the extension to Hernesaari in 2024.\n\n===Kalasatama===\n\nThe construction of new housing in the former harbour area of Kalasatama began in 2011. Kalasatama is served by a metro station, and the city has not built tramways in advance of the housing in Kalasatama in the way it has done in J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari. At least two tram lines are planned to be extended into the Kalasatama area, one from the city centre in the south over new bridges (alignment to be decided), and one from the west from H\u00e4meentie.<ref name=\"FTS45\" /><ref name=\"KSVLaajasalo\">[[#KSVLaajasalo|Helsingin kaupunki: Kaupunkisuunnitteluvirasto]]</ref><ref name=\"misc9\">[[#notemisc9|Antero Alku]]</ref> As of May 2015, these are to be completed in 2021 and 2023 (see [[#funding|Funding plan]]).\n\n===Laajasalo===\n{{Main|Crown Bridges}}\n\nThe city council of Helsinki decided on 31 August 2016 to build a tramway to the island of [[Laajasalo]],<ref name=\"HSKruunu\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hs.fi/kaupunki/a1472610018970|title=Helsingin kaupunginvaltuusto p\u00e4\u00e4tti: Kruunuvuorenrantaan rakennetaan Suomen pisin siltayhteys|publisher=Helsingin Sanomat|language=Finnish|accessdate=2016-08-31}}</ref> located to the east of Helsinki city centre. The route will include three new bridges, the longest of which will be the longest in Finland at {{convert|1.2|km|mi}}, and its pylons one of the tallest structures in Helsinki. The bridges will have bicycle and pedestrian lanes in addition to the tramway, but no lanes for private cars. The total length of new double track, including tramways on Laajasalo itself, is about {{convert|10|km|mi}}.<ref name=\"Kruunuhanke\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hel.fi/static/public/hela/Kaupunginhallitus/Suomi/Paatostiedote/2016/Kanslia_2016-08-22_Khs_28_Pt/BF6B4848-9ED5-40C1-9D3B-4E19A93538FA/Liite.pdf|title=Kruunusillat, hankesuunnitelma|publisher=City of Helsinki|language=Finnish|accessdate=2016-08-31}}</ref>\n\n===Ilmala===\n\nLine number 9, opened in August 2008, was originally planned as early as 1990 to link [[Ilmala]] with Merikatu in southern [[Ullanlinna]]. However, in the first phase of construction, the northern part of the route was truncated into It\u00e4-Pasila in order to cut costs, while the southern terminus was placed in Kolmikulma due to opposition to tram tracks by people living along the planned new line.<ref name=\"misc18\"/> The connection to Ilmala in the north was planned in 2008 to be completed in 2013,<ref name=\"Haltia-Holmberg 2008-08-21\"/> but as of 2012, current projections have postponed the completion to 2017.\n\nAlthough shortly before the opening of line 9 HKL stated the continuation to Merikatu had been abandoned permanently,<ref name=\"misc19\">[[#notemisc19|Helsingin kaupungin liikennelaitos]]</ref> within weeks of the opening of the line, extending the route to Merikatu was again proposed, due to complaints from inhabitants of Ullanlinna following the termination of bus line 17. Subsequently, HKL stated they would be \"actively acting to expand the tramline to Merikatu\".<ref name=\"misc20\">[[#notemisc20|Joukkoliikennelautakunta]]</ref> [[interlaced track|Interlacing]] the tracks on some sections on Korkeavuorenkatu is under consideration as a space-saving measure, allowing a larger amount of parking space to be maintained along the street.<ref name=\"HS2008-08-19\">[[#noteHS8|Helsingin Sanomat]]</ref> At the time in 2008, HKL stated that a different line would be routed to Merikatu in the case that line 9 would go to J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari instead.<ref name=\"Ylen aikainen\">[[#ylen_aikainen|Ylen aikainen]]</ref> The southern terminus of line 9 was ultimately extended to the West Harbour ferry terminal in J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari and opened for traffic on 13 August 2012.\n\nIn addition to lengthening the line, moving the line from Kaarlenkatu and Helsinginkatu to Fleminginkatu in Kallio was proposed on 10 October 2008.<ref name=\"Haltia-Holmberg 2008-08-21\"/>\n\n===Munkkivuori===\n\nHelsinki Regional Transport (HSL) has prepared plans for an extension to the residential area of [[Munkkivuori]]. The extension has been debated since the district was built in the 1950s. The bus lines that serve the area carry about 5 million passengers per year as of 2012, which is a sufficient ridership for a tram line. The bus lines have been criticised for being slow and having unpredictable running times. HSL collected comments from the public on several different alignment options in March and April 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hsl.fi/FI/suunnittelu/raitioliikenne/Sivut/Munkkivuori.aspx|title=Munkkivuoren raitiotiet\u00e4 suunnitellaan kev\u00e4\u00e4ll\u00e4 2012|publisher=HRT|accessdate=2012-04-25|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120405163101/http://www.hsl.fi/FI/suunnittelu/raitioliikenne/Sivut/Munkkivuori.aspx|archivedate=2012-04-05}}</ref> However, there is no decision on the funding or construction of the extension.\n\n==Trunk line 550 (\"Jokeri\")==\n\n{{Main|Jokeri light rail}}\n\nThe trunk bus line 550, formerly branded ''Jokeri'' (\"The Joker\", after '''Jo'''ukkoliikenteen '''ke'''h\u00e4m\u00e4inen '''r'''aide'''i'''nvestointi \u2013 \"A circular rail investment for public transportation\"), will be converted to light rail. The city councils of Helsinki and Espoo approved the construction project in June 2016,<ref>http://www.espoo.fi/fi-FI/Asuminen_ja_ymparisto/Valtuuston_paatoksia_1362016(94196)</ref><ref>http://www.hel.fi/static/public/hela/Kaupunginvaltuusto/Suomi/Paatostiedote/2016/Kanslia_2016-06-15_Kvsto_12_Pt/index.html</ref> after the state of Finland decided to participate in funding the construction. The rail line is preliminarily projected to open in 2021.<ref>http://raidejokeri.info/?page_id=47</ref> The construction of the {{convert|25|km|mi|adj=on}} light rail line, without rolling stock or a depot, is projected to cost \u20ac274 million as of June 2016, with rolling stock and a depot projected to additionally cost up to \u20ac95 and \u20ac65 million.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.hel.fi/static/public/hela/Kaupunginvaltuusto/Suomi/Paatostiedote/2016/Kanslia_2016-06-15_Kvsto_12_Pt/A2AEFA90-F3B5-4859-9D57-CD2CF135D0F9/Liite.pdf\n|title=Raide-Jokeri, hankesuunnitelma 2015\n|publisher=Cities of Espoo and Helsinki\n|accessdate=2016-06-16}}</ref>\n\n==Other possibilities==\n\nA private group consisting of members of the Finnish Tramway Society and students of [[Helsinki University of Technology]] drew up plans for a new tram line linking Arabia to Pasila railway station in order to improve the public transport connections of [[Kumpula]].<ref name=\"Alku Kumpula\">[[#Alku Kumpula|Antero Alku]]</ref> The proposed line, provisionally numbered line 5,<ref name=\"Raitiolinja 5\">[[#Raitiolinja 5|Antero Alku, Janne Peltola & Jonas Wahlbeck]]</ref> could either utilise the disused freight railway line in Southern Kumpula<ref name=\"Alku Kumpula\" /> or only existing tram tracks, including a stretch on Sturenkatu between M\u00e4kel\u00e4nkatu and H\u00e4meentie that is presently only used for depot movements.<ref name=\"Raitiolinja 5\" /> The proposal gained public interest,<ref name=\"Helsingin_Uutiset_2009-03-07\">[[#helsingin_uutiset|Helsingin Uutiset]]</ref> and on 4 April 2009 the City Planning Board of Helsinki mandated that an official study would be made on a tram line linking Munkkiniemi to Arabia or Kalasatama via Pasila and Kumpula, with provisions made for further extension of the line to [[Otaniemi]] in the west and to [[Viikki]] in the east.<ref name=\"KSLK 2009-04-02\">[[#KSLK 2009-04-02|Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta]]</ref>\n\nThe possibility of extending the lines 1 and 1A to the [[K\u00e4pyl\u00e4 railway station]] (or further to [[Oulunkyl\u00e4]]) in the north and rerouting the same lines through the unused tracks on [[Linjat]] in [[Kallio]] have been brought up as possible future projects to improve passenger numbers on the unpopular line.<ref name=\"Haltia-Holmberg 2008-09-15\">[[#Haltia-Holmberg 2008-09-15|Mirva Haltia-Holmberg]]</ref> A 2012 proposal for the reorganization of surface traffic after the completion of the \"Pisara\" connection included an extension of line 1 to the K\u00e4pyl\u00e4 station, but for a different reason. The [[Helsinki City Rail Loop]] is an underground loop of the commuter railway network that would distribute passengers to three new underground stations in central Helsinki. The proposal for after the city rail loop construction for surface traffic includes a new bus terminal at K\u00e4pyl\u00e4. Bus lines that currently continue to the city centre would terminate at the K\u00e4pyl\u00e4 station, where the passengers could make a connection to commuter trains or an extended tram line 1.\n\nIn addition to the above, expansion of the tram network from Arabia to [[Viikki]], K\u00e4pyl\u00e4 to [[Koskela]] and Pikku Huopalahti to [[Haaga]] have been mentioned as potential long-term projects.<ref name=\"FTS45\" />\n\nA construction of a light rail or tram system has also been proposed as a possible solution of arranging public transport in the [[\u00d6stersundom]] area [[Annexation|annexed]] by Helsinki from [[Vantaa]] and [[Sipoo]] on 1 January 2009. An extension of the [[Helsinki Metro]] was originally planned as the main form of public transport for this area, but on 20 February 2009 a newspaper reported that a light rail system is being studied as an alternative to supplement or replace the Metro connection to this area due to the lower costs of a light rail link.<ref name=\"Karjalainen\">[[#Karjalainen 2009-02-20|Marketta Karjalainen]]</ref><ref name=\"YLE 2009-06-25\">[[#YLE 2009-06-25|YLE]]</ref> If built, the light rail link could be extended as far east as [[Porvoo]].<ref name=\"YLE 2009-06-25\" /> \u00d6stersundom is located in eastern Helsinki, and as such the proposed new system would be completely unconnected with the currently existing tram system. It could, however, connect with the future Jokeri line in [[It\u00e4keskus]].\n\nThe construction of some of the expansions to the network as [[trolleybus]] lines was studied in a 2009 report by Helsinki City Transport,<ref name=\"HS 2009-04-22\">[[#HS 2009-04-22|Helsingin Sanomat]]</ref><ref name=\"HKL troylleybus report\">[[#HKL troylleybus report|Helsingin Kaupungin Liikennelaitos]]</ref><ref name=\"Haltia-Holmberg 2009-04-30\">[[#Haltia-Holmberg 2009-04-30|Mirva Haltia-Holmberg]]</ref> but the city decided to drop the trolleybus plans for the foreseeable future in 2011.\n\n=={{anchor|funding}}2015 funding plan==\n\nIn April 2015, Helsinki City Transport (HKL) approved a plan for funding tram network projects for 2016-25.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dev.hel.fi/paatokset/media/att/ce/ceca559610054ae3dae56561dab5d52fd507b5a5.pdf|title=Liikenneinvestointien talousarvioehdotus vuodeksi 2016 sek\u00e4 investointiohjelmaehdotus v. 2017-2025|publisher=City of Helsinki|accessdate=2015-05-06}}{{dead link|date=March 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> These plans are subject to continuous reviews and changes. For instance, most of the items listed here are delayed compared to the plan approved in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hel.fi/static/public/hela/Kaupunkisuunnittelulautakunta/Suomi/Esitys/2012/Ksv_2012-04-17_Kslk_13_El/A5618C1A-5A61-4A9B-BA99-7B987A40E8C7/Liite.pdf|title=Liikenneinvestointien talousarvioehdotusvuodeksi 2013 sek\u00e4investointiohjelmaehdotus vuosiksi 2014-17|publisher=City of Helsinki|accessdate=2012-04-25}}</ref> The allocations of funds are in millions of euros.\n\n{|  class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width: 80%;\"\n! Project                              \n! 2015   \n! 2016   \n! 2017   \n! 2018   \n! 2019   \n! 2020\n! 2021\n! 2022\n! 2023\n! 2024\n! 2025\n! style=\"text-align:center; width 10em\" |Total (M\u20ac)\n|-\n|Kruunuvuorenranta bridge (including track and electrification)\n| \n| 0.8\n| 0.8\n| 21.6\n| 32.0\n| 44.1\n| 35.3\n| 17.9\n| 14.0\n| \n| \n| 166.5\n|-\n|Line 9 Pasila\u2013Ilmala\n| \n| 0.3\n| 0.0\n| 1.7\n| 2.2\n| 2.0\n| 1.0\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 7.2\n|- \n|Reijolankatu\n| \n| 0.5\n| 1.0\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 1.5\n|- \n|J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari, extension to new ferry terminal\n| \n| 1.5\n| 0.9\n| 1.2\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 2.3\n|- \n|J\u00e4tk\u00e4saari, V\u00e4limerenkatu\n|\n| 0.1\n| 2.3\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 2.4\n|- \n|Telakkakatu \u2013 Eiranranta\n| \n| 1.0\n| 2.1\n| 1.7\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 4.8\n|- \n|Trunk line 550 (\"Jokeri\")\n| \n| \n| 0.6\n| 4.3\n| 6.4\n| 35.0\n| 35.4\n| 35.4\n| \n| \n| \n| 117.1\n|- \n|Topeliuksenkatu\n|\n|\n|\n| 2.0\n| 2.0\n| 2.2\n| 2.2\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 8.4\n|- \n|Paciuksenkatu grass-surface track\n| \n|\n|\n| 0.4\n| 0.5\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n| 0.9\n|- \n|Meilahti return loop\n|\n|\n|\n| 0.5\n| 0.5\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n| 1.0\n|- \n|Fredrikinkatu, extension to Bulevardi\n|\n|\n|\n|\n| 1.0\n| 1.5\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n| 2.5\n|- \n|Nihti \u2013 Kalasatama center\n|\n|\n|\n|\n| 1.0\n| 2.1\n| 3.2\n|\n|\n|\n|\n| 6.3\n|-\n|Kalasatama center \u2013 H\u00e4meentie\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 2.0\n| 2.0\n| 2.0\n| 3.6\n| \n| \n| 9.6\n|-\n|Eiranranta \u2013 Hernesaari\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n| 0.2\n| 0.5\n| 0.5\n| 0.5\n| \n| 1.7\n|-\n|Vallilanlaakso tramway\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 1.0\n| 1.0\n| 1.6\n| \n| 3.6\n|-\n|Vartiosaari island\n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 0.4\n| 0.4\n| 4.0\n| 4.8\n|-\n|Munkkivuori \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| \n| 0.5\n| 1.5\n| \n| 2.0\n|}\nNotes:\n* The Kruunuvuorenranta bridge is planned to be a future landmark in Helsinki, a 1&nbsp;km long cable-stayed bridge for trams, pedestrians and bicyclists. It is planned to provide a quick connection to the city center from the new district of Kruunuvuorenranta (under construction as of May 2015) as well as existing suburbs on the island of Laajasalo.\n* Trunk line 550 (\"Jokeri\") extends to the Espoo municipality. This plan only covers HKL's investment for part within the borders of Helsinki.\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Trains|Finland}}\n* [[Helsinki Metro]]\n* [[Trams in Finland]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=18em}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n'''Helsinki City Transport'''\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite web\n |url         = http://www.hel.fi/wps/portal/HKL/Artikkeli?WCM_GLOBAL_CONTEXT=/hkl/fi/P__t_ksenteko/Liikennehankkeita/Raitiolinja+9/9_taustaa\n |title       = Historiallinen lis\u00e4ys Helsingin rataverkkoon\n |accessdate  = 2008-08-18\n |date        = 2008-08-08\n |language    = Finnish\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20080913194348/http://www.hel.fi/wps/portal/HKL/Artikkeli?WCM_GLOBAL_CONTEXT=%2Fhkl%2Ffi%2FP__t_ksenteko%2FLiikennehankkeita%2FRaitiolinja+9%2F9_taustaa\n |archivedate = 2008-09-13\n |ref         = notemisc19\n |url-status     = dead\n}}\n* {{cite web\n |url         = http://www.hel.fi/wps/wcm/connect/de137f804a173581acf7ec3d8d1d4668/D_2_2009_Johdinautoliikenteen+toteutettavuusselvitys.pdf?MOD=AJPERES\n |title       = Johdinautoliikenteen toteutettavuusselvitys\n |accessdate  = 2009-05-04\n |year        = 2009\n |language    = Finnish\n |format      = PDF\n |ref         = HKL troylleybus report\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20110611113329/http://www.hel.fi/wps/wcm/connect/de137f804a173581acf7ec3d8d1d4668/D_2_2009_Johdinautoliikenteen+tote