{"title_page": "Miggs Cuaderno", "text_new": "{{short description|Filipino child actor and TV host}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Miggs Cuaderno\n| image              = https://www.google.com.ph/url?sa=i&source=web&cd=&ved=2ahUKEwjvtLGw3PzmAhWB9XMBHbcEBAoQjhx6BAgBEAI&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fcuadernomiggs&psig=AOvVaw23XpSexoKquku238tzPVDu&ust=1578872453763275\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Miggs Cuaderno\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|2004|08|08}}\n| birth_place        = [[Philippines]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| occupation         = [[Teen Actor]], [[Student]], [[TV Host]] [[Multi Awarded Actor]] [[Child Actor]]\n| agent              = [[GMA Network]]\n| television         = \n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| relatives          = \n| imagesize          = \n| othername          = Miggs\n| alma mater         = \n| yearsactive        = 2009-present\n}}\n'''Miggs Cuaderno''' (born August 8, 2004) is a child actor and has won 13 awards including his best actor in paris And the First Child Actor to be awarded A Balanghai Trophy on Cinemalaya X 2014 [[Filipinos|Filipino]] [[child actor]] and known in the [[Philippines]] as a [[TV host]] in [[GMA Network|GMA]]'s ''[[Tropang Potchi]]'' and as an actor in GMA television series, Ang Munting Heredera as Ton Ton, [[Second Chances (2015 TV series)|''Second Chances'']], which stars [[Jennylyn Mercado]], [[Raymart Santiago]], [[Camille Prats]], and [[Rafael Rosell]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/cuadernomiggs|title=Miggs Cuaderno (@cuadernomiggs) {{!}} Twitter|website=twitter.com|language=en|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref> He was also known for ''[[Poor Se\u00f1orita]]'' as Apol, Prima Donnas as Coco'', Destiny Rose as Young Joey, Quick Change and Asintado.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4581736/|title=Miggs Cuaderno|website=IMDb|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref>\n\nIn the [[Ch\u00e9ries-Ch\u00e9ris]] International Film Festival in France, Miggs Cuaderno won a best actor award in a Cinemalaya film, ''Quick Changes.''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/artistcenter/videos/2014-12-11/75/Congratulations-Miggs-Cuaderno|title=Congratulations, Miggs Cuaderno! {{!}} GMANetwork.com - Artist Center - Videos|last=Inc.|first=GMA New Media|access-date=2017-03-04|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=GMA Network|title=Congratulations, Miggs Cuaderno|date=2014-12-11|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XbBNpc-VWQQ|accessdate=2017-03-04}}</ref>\n\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Type of Role\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Prima Donnas]]\n|Coco\n|Supporting Role / Antagonist\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Kambal, Karibal]]''\n|James\n|Supporting Role\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Magpakailanman|Magpakailanman: Batang Bihag]]''\n|Jack Jack\n|Main Role\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2016\n|''[[Tsuperhero]]''\n|Bokutox / Bok\n|Supporting Role\n|-\n|''[[Magpakailanman|Magpakailanman: The Abused Boy]]'' \n|Makmak\n|Episode Role\n|-\n|''[[Poor Se\u00f1orita]]''\n|Apol\n|Main Role\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2015\n|''[[Magpakailanman|Magpakailanman: Batang Isinilang sa Bilanguan]]''\n|Paul Oliver\n|Episode Role\n|-\n|''[[Destiny Rose]]''\n|Joselito Vergara Jr. / young Joey\n|Special Participation\n|-\n|''[[My Mother's Secret]]''\n|Mac\n|Supporting Role\n|-\n|''[[Magpakailanman|Magpakailanman: Pasan ko, kapatid ko]]''\n|Angelo\n|Episode Role\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2014\n|''[[My BFF (TV series)|My BFF]]''\n|Red Catacutan\n|Supporting Role\n|-\n|''[[Magpakailanman|Magpakailanman: 3 Episodes]]''\n|Gerald / Rolly / Alvin\n|Episode Role\n|-\n|''[[Kambal Sirena]]''\n|young Jun\n|Special Participation\n|-\n|''[[The Ryzza Mae Show]]''\n|Himself / Guest\n|Guest\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2013\n|''[[Magpakailanman|Magpakailanman: Biktima o Estapadora]]'' \n|Makmak\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Episode Role\n|-\n|''[[Magpakailanman|Magpakailanman: Sa Kabila ng Hirap]]'' \